==English==

===Etymology===
''Cease'' essentially meaning "stop", and ''desist'' meaning "do not do it again."

===Expression===
'''cease and desist'''

#''Law.'' The legal term used in demands for an entity to permanently stop doing something (or to ''cease and desist from'' doing it).

===Adjective===
'''cease-and-desist'''

#''Law.'' Demanding that one "ceases and desists from" continuing certain behavior, such as [[copyright infringement]], [[trademark infringement]], [[slander]], or [[libel]].
